WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.669
- All right, hey
everyone, it's Mark Wiens.

00:00:01.669 --> 00:00:04.432
I am in Saigon, Ho Chi Min City, Vietnam,

00:00:04.432 --> 00:00:07.495
and I'm sitting down for what is one of,

00:00:07.495 --> 00:00:09.829
I guess you could call it a pastime

00:00:09.829 --> 00:00:12.829
or a highly enjoyed meal in Vietnam,

00:00:14.821 --> 00:00:16.321
uh, eating snails.

00:00:17.527 --> 00:00:20.277
(chillout beats)

00:00:22.357 --> 00:00:26.281
So first, you choose your
type of shellfish or snail.

00:00:26.281 --> 00:00:29.850
And then once you know
which snail you want,

00:00:29.850 --> 00:00:32.731
then you tell them how you want it cooked.

00:00:32.731 --> 00:00:34.827
So, they have like five
different ways to cook it,

00:00:34.827 --> 00:00:37.744
I think one is stir-fried, sauteed,

00:00:39.183 --> 00:00:42.404
steamed, a bunch of different ways.

00:00:42.404 --> 00:00:45.272
But this is like a Vietnamese pastime,

00:00:45.272 --> 00:00:47.125
it's extremely popular,

00:00:47.125 --> 00:00:50.897
and whenever you eat shellfish and snails

00:00:50.897 --> 00:00:53.003
you have to be drinking beer as well.

00:00:53.003 --> 00:00:55.586
At least, almost everyone does.

00:00:58.474 --> 00:01:01.298
So I am sitting right along the street,

00:01:01.298 --> 00:01:04.747
actually just a couple blocks
from where I'm staying,

00:01:04.747 --> 00:01:07.635
and I have ordered a
couple of different dishes

00:01:07.635 --> 00:01:09.786
of which a few I know what they are,

00:01:09.786 --> 00:01:11.379
and a few I have no idea what they are.

00:01:11.379 --> 00:01:13.331
Oh, and one that just came.

00:01:13.331 --> 00:01:14.164
Ohh-kay.

00:01:16.091 --> 00:01:17.850
Oh, these are the crazy ones.

00:01:17.850 --> 00:01:19.703
I'm not sure what kind of snail this is

00:01:19.703 --> 00:01:21.412
but it was recommended by our waiter.

00:01:21.412 --> 00:01:22.857
This is a huge--

00:01:22.857 --> 00:01:24.589
that's huge.

00:01:24.589 --> 00:01:27.423
Comparison of this one and this one.

00:01:27.423 --> 00:01:28.706
Oh, that's hot.

00:01:28.706 --> 00:01:29.815
Oh that's hot.

00:01:29.815 --> 00:01:33.898
Okay, I'm gonna grab these
little two-prong fork.

00:01:35.070 --> 00:01:36.140
I think I'm gonna start with--

00:01:36.140 --> 00:01:39.277
I think these are the Babylon snails,

00:01:39.277 --> 00:01:42.636
or Babylon snai--
yeah, I think so.

00:01:42.636 --> 00:01:46.299
Anyways, and this is
stir-fried in chili and garlic.

00:01:46.299 --> 00:01:49.216
Okay, let me poke it and then pull.

00:01:52.011 --> 00:01:55.212
Oh yeah, okay that came out nicely.

00:01:55.212 --> 00:01:58.917
Okay so the problem is
that all the seasoning

00:01:58.917 --> 00:02:01.210
is on the shell, but
then when I pulled it out

00:02:01.210 --> 00:02:04.620
it's like a naked, a little naked snail.

00:02:04.620 --> 00:02:08.348
So, I don't know if I
should dip in a sauce?

00:02:08.348 --> 00:02:10.598
Okay I'll dip a little bit,

00:02:11.490 --> 00:02:14.157
and then I'm gonna eat it, okay.

00:02:17.734 --> 00:02:18.567
Mmmm.

00:02:20.588 --> 00:02:21.724
Oh wow.

00:02:21.724 --> 00:02:22.557
That is--

00:02:24.570 --> 00:02:27.491
it's a little bit on the chewy side,

00:02:27.491 --> 00:02:30.423
but I do like that seasoning.

00:02:30.423 --> 00:02:32.983
The seasoning is like garlic salt--

00:02:32.983 --> 00:02:35.233
garlic salt and chili, mmm.

00:02:37.451 --> 00:02:39.590
Oh that's chewy, but in a very good way.

00:02:39.590 --> 00:02:41.507
Almost like squid, mmm.

00:02:42.590 --> 00:02:47.162
Okay, this one is another
snail and I can see--

00:02:47.162 --> 00:02:50.427
and this one I think is
stewed in coconut milk,

00:02:50.427 --> 00:02:55.132
and then it is topped with a
handful of Vietnamese mint,

00:02:55.132 --> 00:02:57.492
or Vietnamese coriander.

00:02:57.492 --> 00:02:58.981
Let me try to find a big one.

00:02:58.981 --> 00:03:00.398
Okay, here we go.

00:03:02.081 --> 00:03:02.914
Wow.

00:03:06.174 --> 00:03:07.683
I didn't even know how to eat this,

00:03:07.683 --> 00:03:09.778
but the kind waiters here have told me

00:03:09.778 --> 00:03:11.433
that I gotta suck this one,

00:03:11.433 --> 00:03:13.120
'cause I was trying to poke down here,

00:03:13.120 --> 00:03:15.620
but there was nothing to poke.

00:03:18.864 --> 00:03:19.781
Mmmm, okay.

00:03:21.650 --> 00:03:24.733
I sucked down a bunch of sauce first.

00:03:25.852 --> 00:03:29.338
And then the little snail came
like, sliming out at the end.

00:03:29.338 --> 00:03:31.644
That almost has the texture of an oyster.

00:03:31.644 --> 00:03:34.401
It's slimy, and then that's like

00:03:34.401 --> 00:03:37.484
a kind of a sweet coconut milk curry.

00:03:38.614 --> 00:03:42.781
I think I should chase it
with some Vietnamese mint.

00:03:45.100 --> 00:03:47.670
Mmm, once you're finished
eating these snails,

00:03:47.670 --> 00:03:51.587
you just toss the shell
into the garbage below.

